quran[31]{c,v,t,f}:
  74,43,"They will say, "
  74,44,"Nor did we used to feed the poor."
  74,45,"And we used to enter into vain discourse with those who engaged [in it],"
  75,40,"Is not that [Creator] Able to give life to the dead?"
  77,31,"[But having] no cool shade and availing not against the flame."
  77,32,"Indeed, it throws sparks [as huge] as a fortress,"
  77,33,"As if they were yellowish [black] camels."
  78,28,"And denied Our verses with [emphatic] denial."
  78,29,"But all things We have enumerated in writing."
  78,30,"",footnotes:1:[This announcement will be made to the companions of Hell.]
  79,22,"Then he turned his back, striving [i.e., plotting].{1}",footnotes:1:[An alternative meaning is "running [from the snake]."]
  79,23,"And he gathered [his people] and called out."
  79,24,"And said, "
  80,19,"From a sperm-drop He created him and destined for him;{1}",footnotes:1:[His proportions, provisions, life span, etc.]
  80,20,"Then He eased the way for him;{1}",footnotes:1:[Into this world (i.e., his birth) . It may also refer to life itself, which has been made easier by Allāh's guidance.]
  80,21,"Then He causes his death and provides a grave for him.{1}",footnotes:1:[To conceal his decaying body.]
  81,16,"Those that run [their courses] and disappear [i.e., set]"
  81,17,"And by the night as it closes in{1}",footnotes:1:[An alternative meaning is "as it departs."]
  81,18,"And by the dawn when it breathes [i.e., stirs]"
  82,10,"And indeed, [appointed] over you are keepers,{1}",footnotes:1:[Angels who preserve the deeds of men in records.]
  82,11,"Noble and recording;"
  82,12,"They know whatever you do."
  83,7,"No! Indeed, the record of the wicked is in sijjeen."
  83,8,"And what can make you know what is sijjeen?"
  83,9,"It is [their destination{1} recorded in] a register inscribed.",footnotes:1:[The lowest depths of Hell.]
  84,4,"And has cast out that within it{1} and relinquished [it].",footnotes:1:[Of the dead and all else buried therein.]
  84,5,"And has listened [i.e., responded] to its Lord and was obligated [to do so] -"
  84,6,"O mankind, indeed you are laboring toward your Lord with [great] exertion{1} and will meet it.{2}",footnotes:1:[i.e., striving throughout your life until you meet your Lord, hastening toward death.],footnotes:2:[i.e., you will find all that you intended and accomplished awaiting you in the Hereafter. Another meaning is \"And will meet Him [i.e., your Lord]\" and be recompensed in full by Him.]
  85,1,"By the sky containing great stars"
  85,2,"And [by] the promised Day"
  85,3,"And [by] the witness and what is witnessed,"
